Entertainment today's story is, strictly speaking, not a news story, because it lacks more detail and, with some of the author's points of view, is more like an interview essay. The members of entertainment magazine are not professional journalists and can not go into the front line, but they are trying to communicate with different organizations or individuals on the front line, hoping to see the prevention and control of the epidemic from the perspective of the rescuers.

On Jan. 23, Bai Yi, a college student at N University, set up a wechat group with friends who were also concerned about the Wuhan outbreak. But the action of Bai Yi does not stop at"Chat"just.

After learning of the shortage of supplies in local hospitals in Wuhan, she immediately bought goggles on Taobao to donate to Wuhan, and kept up to date with news of shops and express delivery on her friends'circle, so many friends joined in. Friends within the high degree of attention and high interaction to let Bai Yi feel that more people can mobilize the power to form a total, to reduce the local Wuhan receiving material workload.

So, she and her friend Xiao Chen decided to gather together to donate money and goods to the good people, buy more materials to help Wuhan. Chen relayed the news to a local high school student's model United Nations Convention Organization, and drew on the experience of model United's campaign, which quickly made the donation campaign work as a project.

Bai Yi and Xiao Chen, in this way to non-charitable identity, relying on a non-charity, temporary organization of a fund-raising group. By about 2 p.m. on Jan. 25, they had raised about 60,000 Renminbi, or about fifty-five thousand Renminbi, in donations to 13 hospitals.

There are a lot of ordinary people, do with Bai Yi and Xiao Chen the same thing. Eve, a college student, joined a volunteer wechat group on Jan. 24. Although she is new to the group, she is not a new volunteer. She and her early co founders had similar volunteer experiences, such as teaching in Wenchuan County during the earthquake and the Metoo online campaign. Eve's general experience is to find people on the fly, set up volunteer groups, and assign jobs to support operations. In this kind of temporary organization, everyone is not very familiar with, but the experience of similar, to ensure the efficiency of the work.

On New Year's Eve, almost everyone in the circle of friends is reposting fundraising messages from different sources, foreign alumni associations or individuals, in order to donate money and goods to the country. Out of curiosity about the effectiveness of these individuals or organizations, and their actions, I try to reach out to them. After several rounds of communication, I found that these groups, organizations, or individuals face similar difficulties. The biggest problem, and the hardest to solve, is the lack of supplies. Bai Yi and Chen collected goggles and gloves, they found most Taobao shop or manufacturer to provide masks and protective clothing is difficult to meet the standards. Bai told me that they had tried to contact some businesses and manufacturers, said there is no goods. So where's the product? In fact, they were sent to Wuhan at the request of the state.

However, many of the goods sent to Wuhan at the request of the state lagged behind the medical supplies delivered by the non-governmental Organization. However, there are still some embarrassing situations in the folk rescue. For example, at noon on the 25th, Bai Yi contacted a hospital in Wuhan, and the other side mentioned that the materials sent by the state have been implemented and there is no shortage of things for the time being. Some local hospitals in Wuhan do not allow private donations. Bai and Eve team had to choose SF express or other green channel delivery, medical supplies sent directly to the doctor.

Just participated in the Australian mountain fire fund-raising Campaign@yunwu, in the local difficult to buy masks, still managed to buy some supplies, intend to donate to Wuhan. Before January 24, a series of documents issued by Hubei Province showed that the government did not accept donations from abroad for the time being. Cloud five can only through the Red Cross, Wuhan Customs, Hubei Health Commission and other institutions, hope to send goods to the domestic. Red Cross, Wuhan Customs can not provide contact information for overseas donations, Hubei Health Commission specifically stressed the rejection of overseas donations. Under the policy, or in the case of failed contact agencies, some of Sydney's Chinese doctors brought supplies into the country from the Xiamen port to Wuhan. It's a classic curve save.

The structures of some of these self-organized groups, are much more astute, and they have a keen eye for government bailouts and even media underreporting. Eve's team believes that currently, in addition to Wuhan, Hubei Province in other cities or regions of the support force is very weak, media coverage of the surrounding cities in Wuhan, obviously insufficient attention. So they targeted the cities around Wuhan, such as Jingzhou and Huangshi.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In this year's relief effort, I found that some of the practices of local governments have backfired on the effectiveness of civil aid and voluntary action. The outbreak, at least in Wuhan before and after a few days, the volunteers with their experience and ability, almost walked onto the stage center. Some of its features, such as temporary organization, flexible organization, folk channels and extensive network of contacts, have been honed in previous activities, and have played a role in the face of the government of Hubei, which has lagged in its response. The front and the rear, within the limits of compliance, reached an almost unmediated union. It communicates directly with the hospital and even with individual doctors, and the volunteers are now the ones who know the actual situation of the Hubei Hospital's supplies best, in addition to the medical staff. With the extremely advanced means of communication in this era, volunteers can be organized in different parts of the country to reduce the cost of participating in voluntary activities, while the rapid development of express logistics driven by E-commerce, was the last ditch for the medics after the city was shut down.

With the help of the action logic close to "neighborhood mutual help" , and spontaneity, volunteers can effectively rectify and supplement systems and corners that are not taken into account by the official, or bureaucratic, system. In this outbreak, these "supplements" , or "corrective" actions by non-governmental forces, dispel or reinforce the government's perception and mentality of the relative distrust of ngos or non-governmental organizations? That remains to be seen. Of course, I don't deny that there are some problems with voluntary contributions themselves, such as the excessive source of resources will cause an increase in the workload of the hospital, and donated materials do not meet the standards of medical use, may be rejected by the hospital.

After writing this observation note, Yun Wu's diary, "overseas donations to Wuhan, red light everywhere, " published on Douban was deleted. I also reached out to a guide working in Thailand, who, along with her peers, donated a large amount of supplies of face masks to the affected areas. On the morning of the 26th, several more tour guides had just returned to China wearing masks. We are seeing, and we are seeing, how civil aid groups and volunteers are involved in writing this page of history.

(the names are pseudonyms. Instructor: Wu Changchang)
